    {
      "Text": "An update for hadoop is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1.",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Apache Hadoop is a framework that allows for the distributed processing of large data sets across clusters of computers using simple programming models. It is designed to scale up from single servers to thousands of machines, each offering local computation and storage.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nIn Apache Hadoop 3.2.0 to 3.2.1, 3.0.0-alpha1 to 3.1.3, and 2.0.0-alpha to 2.10.0, WebHDFS client might send SPNEGO authorization header to remote URL without proper verification.(CVE-2020-9492)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for hadoop is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of high. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "High",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "hadoop",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
